      • condenseRecords

        public void condenseRecords()
        This method condenses the records, converting all single records (ranged records are converted back to single records through the toArray method in Record) back to as many ranged records as possible and then storing the single records that could not be converted to ranged records. Example: Let's say we have records [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 66, 77] and the ranged records [4:7, 12:17]. The output will now be [1:3, 4:7, 12:17, 66, 77].

      • simplifyRecords

        public void simplifyRecords()
        This method simplifies the records, converting the single records and the ranged records to an ordered array of single records.

        Example: Let's say we have records [1, 2, 3] and the ranged records [4:7, 12:17]. The output will now be [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 12, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17].
